                <div>
                    <p>
                        With everyone on board with the majority of the new concepts, it was time to start refining the actual UI elements. It was also the perfect timing to transition from <b>Adobe Illustrator</b>, which was until then the official tool for mockups, towards <b>Sketch</b>, a much better tool for interface design that came with shared design libraries as much needed addition.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The other benefit was a tight integration with Principle, which made creating higher fidelity prototypes a breeze.
                    </p>
                    </div>
            </article>

