                <div>
                    <p>
                        As a consultant, your stay on a company is always on a time limit, and by the Summer of 2017, Ericsson decided to start building up their in-house design team, to better prepare for a more design driven future.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        By the end of the year, the <b>Ericsson Design System</b> that grew from the team's experience creating the tech stack agnostic <b>Loki</b> CSS/JS framework and the UX vision work we did for the new brand, was awarded a <a href="https://www.ericsson.com/en/press-releases/2018/8/ericsson-wins-red-dot-awards-for-brand-and-interface-design" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Red Dot Design Award</a> and an <a href="https://ifworlddesignguide.com/entry/256283-ericsson-design-system" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IF Design Award</a>.
                    </p>
